bacterial vaginosis does anyone know what the symptons are also what is the cause and how can it be treated hi ambertottie yes bacterial vaginosis is an abnormal vaginal condition that is most often recognized by a fishy vaginal discharge the symptoms of bacterial vaginosis are a foul fishy odor and a grayish white discharge the amount of the discharge varies so there is no amount that is considered normal there are no other symptoms if you have a vaginal discharge that is abnormal for you it is a good idea to see a health practitioner to rule out all other conditions some women with bacterial vaginosis will experience no symptoms at all please look article http www askedweb com askedweb fishy vaginal odor bacterial vaginosis the most common treatment for bacterial vaginosis is antibiotics usually one course of treatment is successful a small percentage of women will experience recurrent symptoms within a month consequently a second course of antibiotics will be prescribed but you need know that taking antibiotics to cure this problem will almost absolutely cause another problem yeast infection ask your doc about problem jason homan Chronic fatigue syndrome AIDS Candidiasis Urinary incontinence Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Psoriasis Antibiotic Conjunctivitis Diarrhea Gonorrhoea Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Toxic shock syndrome Common cold Prostate cancer Anorexia nervosa Herpes simplex virus Crohn's disease Stomach cancer Sickle-cell disease Ulcerative colitis Sexually-transmitted infection Group A streptococcal infection Diabetes mellitus Epilepsy Medical analysis of circumcision Acne Pelvic inflammatory disease Bipolar disorder Domestic rabbit Hypoglycemia Miscarriage Traditional Chinese medicine Clinical depression Sj__gren's syndrome Autism Cancer Childbirth Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Homeopathy Cephalic disorder Lupus erythematosus Hyperglycemia Allergy Vulvovaginal health Lyme disease Cystic fibrosis Traumatic brain injury Shrimp farm Tuberculos